verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord; Go down to the house of the king of Judah, and speak there this word,
verses.verse_html: 1Thus saith the Lord; Go down to the house of the king of Judah, and speak there this word,

verses.text_plain: And say, Hear the word of the Lord, O king of Judah, that sittest upon the throne of David, thou, and thy servants, and thy people that enter in by these gates:
verses.verse_html: 2And say, Hear the word of the Lord, O king of Judah, that sittest upon the throne of David, thou, and thy servants, and thy people that enter in by these gates:

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord; Execute ye judgment and righteousness, and deliver the spoiled out of the hand of the oppressor: and do no wrong, do no violence to the stranger, the fatherless, nor the widow, neither shed innocent blood in this place.
verses.verse_html: 3Thus saith the Lord; Execute ye judgment and righteousness, and deliver the spoiled out of the hand of the oppressor: and do no wrong, do no violence to the stranger, the fatherless, nor the widow, neither shed innocent blood in this place.

verses.text_plain: For if ye do this thing indeed, then shall there enter in by the gates of this house kings sitting upon the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, he, and his servants, and his people.
verses.verse_html:
4For if ye do this thing indeed, then shall there enter in by the gates of this house kings sitting upon the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, he, and his servants, and his people. ▼
▼ upon…: Heb. for David upon his throne

footnotes.body_text: ▼ upon…: Heb. for David upon his throne
footnotes.body_html: ▼ upon…: Heb. for David upon his throne

verses.text_plain: But if ye will not hear these words, I swear by myself, saith the Lord, that this house shall become a desolation.
verses.verse_html: 5But if ye will not hear these words, I swear by myself, saith the Lord, that this house shall become a desolation.

tokens.text: But if ye will not hear

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord unto the king’s house of Judah; Thou art Gilead unto me, and the head of Lebanon: yet surely I will make thee a wilderness, and cities which are not inhabited.
verses.verse_html: 6For thus saith the Lord unto the king’s house of Judah; Thou art Gilead unto me, and the head of Lebanon: yet surely I will make thee a wilderness, and cities which are not inhabited.

verses.text_plain: And I will prepare destroyers against thee, every one with his weapons: and they shall cut down thy choice cedars, and cast them into the fire.
verses.verse_html: 7And I will prepare destroyers against thee, every one with his weapons: and they shall cut down thy choice cedars, and cast them into the fire.

verses.text_plain: And many nations shall pass by this city, and they shall say every man to his neighbour, Wherefore hath the Lord done thus unto this great city?
verses.verse_html: 8And many nations shall pass by this city, and they shall say every man to his neighbour, Wherefore hath the Lord done thus unto this great city?

verses.text_plain: Then they shall answer, Because they have forsaken the covenant of the Lord their God, and worshipped other gods, and served them.
verses.verse_html: 9Then they shall answer, Because they have forsaken the covenant of the Lord their God, and worshipped other gods, and served them.

verses.text_plain: Weep ye not for the dead, neither bemoan him: but weep sore for him that goeth away: for he shall return no more, nor see his native country.
verses.verse_html: 10Weep ye not for the dead, neither bemoan him: but weep sore for him that goeth away: for he shall return no more, nor see his native country.

verses.text_plain: For thus saith the Lord touching Shallum the son of Josiah king of Judah, which reigned instead of Josiah his father, which went forth out of this place; He shall not return thither any more:
verses.verse_html: 11For thus saith the Lord touching Shallum the son of Josiah king of Judah, which reigned instead of Josiah his father, which went forth out of this place; He shall not return thither any more:

verses.text_plain: But he shall die in the place whither they have led him captive, and shall see this land no more.
verses.verse_html: 12But he shall die in the place whither they have led him captive, and shall see this land no more.

tokens.text: whither they have led him captive

verses.text_plain: Woe unto him that buildeth his house by unrighteousness, and his chambers by wrong; that useth his neighbour’s service without wages, and giveth him not for his work;
verses.verse_html: 13Woe unto him that buildeth his house by unrighteousness, and his chambers by wrong; that useth his neighbour’s service without wages, and giveth him not for his work;

verses.text_plain: That saith, I will build me a wide house and large chambers, and cutteth him out windows; and it is cieled with cedar, and painted with vermilion.
verses.verse_html:
14That saith, I will build me a wide house and large chambers, and cutteth him out windows; and it is cieled with cedar, and painted with vermilion. ▼
▼ large: Heb. through-aired
 , ▼
▼ windows: or, my windows

footnotes.body_html: ▼ windows: or, my windows

verses.text_plain: Shalt thou reign, because thou closest thyself in cedar? did not thy father eat and drink, and do judgment and justice, and then it was well with him?
verses.verse_html: 15Shalt thou reign, because thou closest thyself in cedar? did not thy father eat and drink, and do judgment and justice, and then it was well with him?

verses.text_plain: He judged the cause of the poor and needy; then it was well with him: was not this to know me? saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16He judged the cause of the poor and needy; then it was well with him: was not this to know me? saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: But thine eyes and thine heart are not but for thy covetousness, and for to shed innocent blood, and for oppression, and for violence, to do it.
verses.verse_html:
17But thine eyes and thine heart are not but for thy covetousness, and for to shed innocent blood, and for oppression, and for violence, to do it. ▼
▼ violence: or, incursion

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah; They shall not lament for him, saying, Ah my brother! or, Ah sister! they shall not lament for him, saying, Ah lord! or, Ah his glory!
verses.verse_html: 18Therefore thus saith the Lord concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah; They shall not lament for him, saying, Ah my brother! or, Ah sister! they shall not lament for him, saying, Ah lord! or, Ah his glory!

verses.text_plain: He shall be buried with the burial of an ass, drawn and cast forth beyond the gates of Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 19He shall be buried with the burial of an ass, drawn and cast forth beyond the gates of Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: Go up to Lebanon, and cry; and lift up thy voice in Bashan, and cry from the passages: for all thy lovers are destroyed.
verses.verse_html: 20Go up to Lebanon, and cry; and lift up thy voice in Bashan, and cry from the passages: for all thy lovers are destroyed.

verses.text_plain: I spake unto thee in thy prosperity; but thou saidst, I will not hear. This hath been thy manner from thy youth, that thou obeyedst not my voice.
verses.verse_html:
21I spake unto thee in thy prosperity; but thou saidst, I will not hear. This hath been thy manner from thy youth, that thou obeyedst not my voice. ▼
▼ prosperity: Heb. prosperities

verses.text_plain: The wind shall eat up all thy pastors, and thy lovers shall go into captivity: surely then shalt thou be ashamed and confounded for all thy wickedness.
verses.verse_html: 22The wind shall eat up all thy pastors, and thy lovers shall go into captivity: surely then shalt thou be ashamed and confounded for all thy wickedness.

tokens.text: surely then shalt thou be ashamed

verses.text_plain: O inhabitant of Lebanon, that makest thy nest in the cedars, how gracious shalt thou be when pangs come upon thee, the pain as of a woman in travail!
verses.verse_html:
23O inhabitant of Lebanon, that makest thy nest in the cedars, how gracious shalt thou be when pangs come upon thee, the pain as of a woman in travail! ▼
▼ inhabitant: Heb. inhabitress

tokens.text: as of a woman in travail

verses.text_plain: As I live, saith the Lord, though Coniah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah were the signet upon my right hand, yet would I pluck thee thence;
verses.verse_html: 24As I live, saith the Lord, though Coniah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah were the signet upon my right hand, yet would I pluck thee thence;

verses.text_plain: And I will give thee into the hand of them that seek thy life, and into the hand of them whose face thou fearest, even into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, and into the hand of the Chaldeans.
verses.verse_html: 25And I will give thee into the hand of them that seek thy life, and into the hand of them whose face thou fearest, even into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, and into the hand of the Chaldeans.

verses.text_plain: And I will cast thee out, and thy mother that bare thee, into another country, where ye were not born; and there shall ye die.
verses.verse_html: 26And I will cast thee out, and thy mother that bare thee, into another country, where ye were not born; and there shall ye die.

tokens.text: And I will cast thee out

verses.text_plain: But to the land whereunto they desire to return, thither shall they not return.
verses.verse_html:
27But to the land whereunto they desire to return, thither shall they not return. ▼
▼ desire: Heb. lift up their mind

footnotes.body_text: ▼ desire: Heb. lift up their mind
footnotes.body_html: ▼ desire: Heb. lift up their mind

verses.text_plain: Is this man Coniah a despised broken idol? is he a vessel wherein is no pleasure? wherefore are they cast out, he and his seed, and are cast into a land which they know not?
verses.verse_html: 28Is this man Coniah a despised broken idol? is he a vessel wherein is no pleasure? wherefore are they cast out, he and his seed, and are cast into a land which they know not?

verses.text_plain: O earth, earth, earth, hear the word of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 29O earth, earth, earth, hear the word of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, Write ye this man childless, a man that shall not prosper in his days: for no man of his seed shall prosper, sitting upon the throne of David, and ruling any more in Judah.
verses.verse_html: 30Thus saith the Lord, Write ye this man childless, a man that shall not prosper in his days: for no man of his seed shall prosper, sitting upon the throne of David, and ruling any more in Judah.
